Towns name comes from "Ptoco," a Chickasaw word meaning healing, and "wawa," a Choctaw word for water.
Indians claimed the water could heal braves wounded in battle.
This mural, the only WPA mural in Panola and one of a few in the state, depicts a cotton field scene: a river, a gin, and a steamboat on the river.
